            <thetext>Patterns like yyyyMMdd do not reliably reject invalid data when parsing. Reason is that most pattern groups, including year, accept less than the given number of digts.

Because of this &quot;1931&quot; is accepted as 01-Jan-2031: Two digts (19) for year, one each for month and day.

Commited patch to 0.7 for pattern YYYY, meaning &quot;year which must be 4 digits long&quot;, as talked about on the phone.</thetext>
